OL,3,CWelsh Bible printed in 1588 to go on
OL,4,Cdisplay in Wales for first time
OL,6,FIt was translated by Bishop William
OL,7,FMorgan when Queen Elizabeth I was
OL,8,Fmonarch as part of an effort to bring
OL,9,Fscriptures to people in languages they
OL,10,Funderstood.
OL,12,FIt is believed that the Bible has
OL,13,Fnever been on public display, although
OL,14,Fit was used in a service at St Benet
OL,15,FPaul's Wharf ` a church in London with
OL,16,Fa long association with the Welsh
OL,17,Fcommunity ` in 1988.
