OL,3,CWelsh Bible printed in 1588 to go on
OL,4,Cdisplay in Wales for first time
OL,6,F"It is a special treasure of the Welsh
OL,7,Flanguage, and we are honoured to have
OL,8,Fit in St Davids Cathedral."
OL,10,FWilliam Morgan had been commissioned
OL,11,Fto produce a standard Welsh edition of
OL,12,Fthe Bible by bringing together
OL,13,Fprevious translations of parts of the
OL,14,Fbook.
OL,16,FHe travelled to London to oversee the
OL,17,Fbooks go through the press, a process
OL,18,Fwhich lasted several weeks because the
OL,19,Fprint workers did not speak Welsh.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/8
