OL,3,CWelsh Bible printed in 1588 to go on
OL,4,Cdisplay in Wales for first time
OL,6,F"It is in remarkably good condition.
OL,7,FThe plan was to print 900 copies, with
OL,8,Fthe idea for every chapel and church
OL,9,Fin Wales to have a copy of the Welsh
OL,10,FBible.
OL,12,F"Because they were used weekly or even
OL,13,Fdaily, the ones that survive in Wales
OL,14,Fare not in such good condition."
OL,16,FDr Trowles described how the Bible was
OL,17,Foriginally kept on the bookshelves of
OL,18,Fthe abbey library, to which it was
OL,19,Fchained so it could not be removed,
OL,20,Fand bears an early shelf mark.
